Refer to https://docs.deno.com/sandboxes/getting_started/

## Create an organization token

The @deno/sandbox SDK authenticates using the DENO_DEPLOY_TOKEN environment variable. Generate it from Settings â†’ Organization tokens, copy the value, and store it securely. Then export it in your local shell or CI job:
```bash
export DENO_DEPLOY_TOKEN=<your-token>
```

## Install the SDK

The SDK works in both Deno and Node.js environments.

```bash
# Using Deno
deno add jsr:@deno/sandbox

# Using npm
npm install @deno/sandbox

# Using pnpm
pnpm install jsr:@deno/sandbox

# Using yarn
yarn add jsr:@deno/sandbox
```


## Run your sandbox code

```bash
deno -EN --env-file main.ts
```